The paper focuses on computer vision and pattern recognition algorithms for food recognition applications, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The mention of "slice convolution" and "food structure" suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of residual networks and the focus on improving performance suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning for food recognition suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
